-- Samaras Says Return to Drachma Would Be Catastrophic, Bild Says
-- B y   A n g e l a   C u l l e n
-- 2012-05-05T08:57:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-05/samaras-says-return-to-drachma-would-be-catastrophic-bild-says.html
Antonis Samaras, the head of  Greece ’s
New Democracy party, said a return to the drachma would have
“catastrophic consequences” for the Hellenic Republic and the
euro-area as a whole, Bild Zeitung reported.  Samaras, favored to become Greece’s next prime minister
after May 6 elections, said his country will repay bailout loans
and adhere to the principles and goals of the political programs
agreed as part of the rescue deal, the German newspaper cited
the leader as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
